Name: Potted Plant
Desc: Not sure what kind of plant it is.

Desc: The storage rack looks a little bare. A few accessories might endear it to customers more.

Desc: Simple long table with white tablecloth.

Name: Tall Chair
Desc: Simple yet elegant tall chair

Name: Coffee Table
Desc: Common coffee table, with a quaint little flower.

Name: Cafe Floor
Desc: Light-blue floor for the cafe.

Desc: Ceiling with a little light hanging from it.

Name: Cafe Wall
Desc: Simple cafe wall.

Desc: Looks like it has been in use for a long time...

Name: Office Desk

Name: Blinds
Desc: Blinds that lets rows of sunlight through.

Desc: Holds various equipment parts. Looks heavy.

Name: Vending Machine

Desc: Control terminal for the room. Give it a nice hard slap if sparks start flying from it.

Name: Messy Storage Rack
Desc: No one wants to tidy up the mess.

Name: Toilet
Desc: Nice and clean. No need to worry about the smell.

Name: Worktable
Desc: For working on malfunctioning parts.

Name: Bar Stool
Desc: Old bar stool. Don't break it.

Name: Bar Counter
Desc: A beautiful bartender will give this bar counter a brand new look.

Name: Cloth Sofa
Desc: Clean and tidy comes first, comfort second.

Name: Sofa Set
Desc: Connect them to seat even more people.

Name: Poster α
Desc: Poster of a Construct. Not sure why it is from the side.

Name: Poster β
Desc: A poster of Liv.

Name: Poster γ
Desc: A photo of Lucia realizing that the Commandant is taking a photo of her.

Name: Neon Logo
Desc: Neon sign of Gray Raven.

Name: Rack
Desc: A curious storage rack. The top shelf seems to be locked.

Name: Punk Floor
Desc: Floor blocks in punk style.

Name: Punk Ceiling
Desc: Ceiling with exposed metal frame.

Name: Punk Logo Wall
Desc: Very distinctive wall.

Name: Paper Window
Desc: Japanese paper window over a wooden frame. Do not poke it.

Name: Cushion Chair
Desc: Chair with cushioned back.

Name: Potted Bamboo
Desc: Bamboo in a bot, giving the room a sense of elegance.

Name: Sakura Fan
Desc: Wall decoration with cherry blossom print.

Name: Hanging Painting
Desc: Said to be a famous painting, but only part of it remains.

Name: Japanese Shelf
Desc: Elegant shelf with paper windows.

Name: Futon
Desc: Don't catch a cold.

Name: Sakura Screen
Desc: Elegant and discreet, a unique picture of culture.

Name: Katana Stand
Desc: For displaying katanas. Lucia's favorite.

Name: Kotatsu
Desc: Once you go in, you can never get out.

Name: Drinking Table
Desc: There is nothing like a stiff drink and some nice salty snacks after work.

Name: Wooden Tub
Desc: Warm vapors rise from this wooden bathtub. Even Constructs need to keep themselves clean.

Name: Japanese Lantern
Desc: Traditional paper lantern, like the ones that guide the dead into the underworld.

Name: Japanese Floor
Desc: Warm and gentle wooden floor.

Name: Beam Ceiling
Desc: Beam ceiling in traditional style, like the one in izakayas.

Name: Sakura Wall
Desc: Cherry-pink wall. One can almost smell the sweet scent of cherry blossoms.

Name: Cyber Egg
Desc: Futuristic holo-projector, displaying various text and images when switched on.

Name: Retro Floor Lamp
Desc: Minimalist floor lamp in retro style. The outstanding workmanship is apparent upon close inspection.

Name: Double Bed
Desc: Classic double bed made from fine red oak. Very comfortable, but the color of the linens is questionable.

Name: Mistletoe Wreath
Desc: Wreath made from mistletoe, celebrating the Christmas season.

Name: Christmas Gift Pile
Desc: Unopened Christmas gifts. Keep an eye on thieves!

Name: Nightstand
Desc: Classic nightstand with candlestick, books and photo frame.

Name: European Closet
Desc: Large European closet made from red oak. Noble and dignified.

Name: Wall Chandelier
Desc: Wall chandelier with twin candles, bright and warm.

Name: Wall Clock
Desc: Announces the time firmly and reliably. A gentleman's piece.

Name: Fireplace
Desc: Fireplace made from red oak and copper, warming both body and heart.

Name: Lattice Window With Curtain
Desc: The red curtain gives this unremarkable window a remarkable elegance.

Name: Christmas Tree
Desc: A must for Christmas season, with Christmas stockings and tiny bells hanging from it. A sight to behold when lit.

Name: European Sofa
Desc: Minimalist sofa without excessive ornamentation, and is all the more comfortable for it.

Name: Dawn (Oil on Canvas)
Desc: Oil painting titled "Dawn". The rays of the rising sun are depicted with broad, bold brush strokes.

Name: European Bookshelf
Desc: Medium-sized retro bookshelf, with an eye-catching arch design.

Name: Christmas Table
Desc: Red tablecloth on wooden table, complete with turkey and candlesticks.

Name: European Chair
Desc: Minimalist red oak chair with high back. A good manners test.

Name: Cushion Stool
Desc: Short stool with leather cushion. Great for the bedroom, not so much for the guest room.

Name: Tile Floor
Desc: Dark tile floor with a wave pattern that prevents slipping.

Name: Christmas Wall
Desc: Decorated with mistletoe, bells and ribbons. There is even a tiny fireplace built into the wall.

Name: Chandelier Beam
Desc: Classy wooden beam adorned with chandelier, lightning up even the largest rooms.

Name: Floating Kuroro
Desc: Kuroro floats above a bonsai. Is it a model or the real thing?

Name: Trash Cans
Desc: Waste separation is crucial to keep the base's intricate recycling system running at max efficiency.

Name: Triple Toilet
Desc: The result of cutting-edge research across many different fields. The perfect industrial design is intended to help Constructs establish bonds with each other and become comfortable with communal life.

Name: Recharge Station
Desc: Allows for quick recharging of Constructs and vehicles. Despite the high endurance of fusion batteries, it never hurts to have a backup plan.

Name: Camera
Desc: High-performance camera that can record high-definition videos. It can be used on a tripod or handheld.

Name: Motorcycle
Desc: Standard one-seater bike that Constructs use to navigate the vast wasteland, moving from stronghold to stronghold.

Name: Divider
Desc: Want a private space? Order the newly-launched divider!

Name: Lantern Pole
Desc: A pole that has small lanterns hanging on it. Remember not to let Nanami take any one of them.

Name: Chinese Tea Table
Desc: One pot of tea, two lots of dim sum, and a few friends playing chess with you. These are all you need to enjoy your time.

Name: Chinese Armchair
Desc: Although it is very hard, its regular shape can help prevent back pain.

Name: Chinese Desk
Desc: A desk with Four Treasures of the Study on it. Wonder whose work desk is it.

Name: Chinese Bench
Desc: A quaint bench that would be uncomfortable if you don't sit up straight.

Name: Chinese Chest of Drawers
Desc: A big drawer that seems to hold everything you buy in a whole year.

Name: Chinese Cupboard
Desc: A small cabinet with a shelf. Tea leaves, teapots, tea cups and small charcoal stoves can be stored in it.

Name: Earthenware Jar
Desc: An empty jar. Everyone knows drinking is forbidden in the dormitory.

Name: Chinese Plant Stand
Desc: A pear wood plant stand made by a well-known craftsman in the Golden Age. The colored glass bottle placed on it is rumored to be a counterfeit made by 3D printing.

Name: Spring Couplet
Desc: A handwritten spring couplet, one of the few traditions that has survived from the Golden Age to this day.

Name: Teahouse's Flag
Desc: A linen cloth with some ancient words written on it. Would anyone come after hanging this up?

Name: Teahouse's Window Pane
Desc: A Chinese-style window pane, but even though you open it, all you can see is the dormitory's metal walls.

Name: Teahouse's Counter
Desc: A long desk and a good hiding spot when playing hide-and-seek.

Name: Chinese Floor Lamp
Desc: A traditional floor lamp made of wood and rice paper, but the bulb is nuclear.

Name: Chinese Screen
Desc: A screen that depicts people's daily life in a market long before the Golden Age. You will expose your feet when hiding behind it.

Name: Chinese Bed
Desc: A traditional soft bed installed with temperature control system and wireless network, making you never want to leave.

Name: Teahouse's Door
Desc: A traditional door that makes you feel you're stepping into a teahouse.

Name: Hanging Lantern
Desc: A large lantern hung high from the ceiling, filling the whole room with festive atmosphere.

Name: Chinese Carpet
Desc: A traditional carpet. Don't step on it with shoes on!

Name: Church Dome
Desc: A baby blue church dome. The light from the dome is warm and comfortable.

Name: Church Floor
Desc: Those square tiles are Bianca's favorite flooring style.

Name: Church Wall
Desc: A clean, baby blue church wall.

Name: Church Pew
Desc: A wooden pew with a delicate fragrance.

Name: Holy Coffin
Desc: It feels sacred to sleep on it. It can produce dim light to help the user calm the mind. Much softer than it looks.

Name: Church Niche
Desc: A little idol is covered with a book someone left in the niche.

Name: Church Chair
Desc: A single-seater church chair that smells of a mild fragrance.

Name: Church Piano Bench
Desc: A little piano bench tailor-made for the piano. It feels cold when sitting on it.

Name: Church Pulpit
Desc: A church book with many sticky notes lies on the pulpit.

Name: Globe
Desc: Nanami loves to put her finger through the semi-transparent projection globe.

Name: Holy Cross
Desc: A silver cross with a blue ribbon. Church members will pray before it.

Name: Church Piano
Desc: A well-preserved, valuable piano.

Name: Church Fence
Desc: An exquisite white marble fence that is sleek to the touch.

Name: Church Flower Bed
Desc: A flower bed planted with forget-me-nots. It imbues the room with moderate fragrance.

Name: Stained Glass Window
Desc: The stained glass brings more sunlight into the room.

Name: Painting of Snow
Desc: A painting of Father Snow created by Bianca.

Name: Holy Banner
Desc: A light blue banner with a church logo.

Name: Church Secret Wall
Desc: A secret wall that glows dimly. Nobody knows how to open it.

Name: Kowloong Banner

Name: Chessboard Floor

Name: Kowloong Cabin Wall
Desc: The cabin wall of the Nighter's entertaining cabin with a huge Kowloong icon.

Name: Kowloong Bench

Name: Kowloong Folding Bed

Name: Kowloong Rack
Desc: The antiques are attached to the shelf, so they will never fall off even if the shelf is moved around.

Name: Kowloong Cauldron
Desc: The cauldron's core is both heating and filtering the water within, preparing it for drinking, cooking, and bathing.

Desc: A piece that originally represented a "horse". It has been reshaped and given a representation of the "knight" at Nanami's hands.

Desc: A piece that originally represented an "advisor". It has been reshaped and given a representation of the "queen" at Nanami's hands.

Desc: A piece that originally represented a "chariot". It has been reshaped and given a representation of the "rook" at Nanami's hands.

Name: Kowloong Round Window
Desc: A window of the Nighter . It is not made of paper. Please do not poke it.

Name: Trading Panel

Name: Shallow Fish Tank
Desc: A huge fish tank that is installed with a water recirculating system at the bottom. You can even plunge into it and swim for a while.

Name: Island Beam
Desc: Multiple fans dispel the scorching heat on the island.

Name: Island Floor
Desc: A floor that can cool down the room with its special material on the surface. However, it is extremely slippery. Never try to slide on it with slippers!

Name: Coastal Wooden Wall
Desc: A wall made of 100% wood. It fills the air with a refreshing sweet fragrance.

Name: Coastal Wine Cabinet
Desc: Different wines are placed on this wooden cabinet. Nanami and Sophia are prohibited from touching it.

Name: Island Entertainment Table
Desc: An islander's table recreated by the WGAA, coming with a popular board game on the island.

Name: Island Patio Window
Desc: A big patio window that displays a blue sky and clear sea water.

Name: Island Window
Desc: Liv has planted some flowers on the windowsill. You can enjoy a gentle fragrance even when the window is closed.

Name: Island Long Table
Desc: An islander's long table recreated by the WGAA, coming with a set of billiard balls.

Name: Island Sofa
Desc: A comfy shell-shaped sofa. Once you sit in it, you will fall asleep without even noticing it.

Name: Island Mural
Desc: A mural depicting an ocean scene. Who is the painter of it?

Name: Island Swim Ring
Desc: A swim ring with multiple decorations. Can it still float in water?

Name: Island Chair
Desc: An islander's chair recreated by the WGAA. Nothing to write home about.

Name: Island Wall Lamp
Desc: An energy-saving, exquisite lamp that glows warmly on summer nights.

Name: Coastal Bed
Desc: A boat bed with a light smell of sea water.

Name: bilibili TV
Desc: bilibili -(゜-゜)つロ

Name: OPPOreno2
Desc: Various vending machines selling OPPO-branded merchandise. Popular with Constructs.

Name: taptap Console
Desc: Take a break and game with the taptap console.

Name: vivoNEX
Desc: The VIVO computer desk supports a multi-monitor setup, making it the ideal choice for working at home.

Name: Quick Pop
Desc: Delicious Quick Popcorn with large eyes on the package.

Name: Huawei 5G Covered
Desc: Multi-functional "Huawei" communications terminal, known for high transmission speeds and popular among Constructs.

Name: 4399 Game Cartridge
Desc: Tiny box with the numbers "4399" on it. There seems to be a switch on the right.

Name: Black Shark Gaming Console
Desc: A powerful machine with the code name "Black Shark". Nanami is always looking for an opportunity to tear it apart.

Name: Mi Sign
Desc: Bright-colored sign. The words "Mi Gaming" are visible even in the darkness.

Name: MyApp Claw Machine
Desc: Popular despite offering only one kind of doll.

Name: 9game TV
Desc: Shows "9game" when on standby. It is relaxing to look at it on a sofa.

Name: bilibili Sofa
Desc: Sofa with many lazy little TVs lying on it.

Name: bilibili Home Theater
Desc: Equipped with large surround-sound speaker, high-definition TV, and a Lucia figure.

Name: bilibili Floor Lamp
Desc: Admit it, you want to give it and its TV-shaped shade a little shake.

Name: bilibili Cushion
Desc: Soft and comfy, you sink into it when you sit on it.

Name: bilibili Table
Desc: Sit around the table and say "Cheers!"

Name: Nubia Game Box
Desc: Curious box of games for rest and recreation.

Name: Kuroro Thunder Gate
Desc: Designed based on a famous tourism spot on the earth, there is a huge red Kuroro lantern hanging in the middle.

Name: Kuroro Totem
Desc: It is found that humans in ancient times built such totems as serve to symbols and blessings, according to a research from the Association of Art.

Name: Kuroro Opera House
Desc: A sail-shaped theater building on the earth. But for some reason, there seems to be a Kuroro standing there.

Name: Kuroro Temple
Desc: A model based on a temple building on Earth.

Name: Kuroro Needle
Desc: A model based on a landmark building on Earth.

Name: Great Kuroro Sphinx
Desc: A golden model made according to historical and archaeological records, but its face looks a bit familiar…

Name: Big Kuroro
Desc: Ding-dong, ding-dong. Kuroro chimes for you.

Name: Kuroro City Ruins
Desc: An ornament made in accordance with an archeological site on Earth. A mysterious image will be projected on it.

Name: Celica with Pearl Earrings
Desc: The painting depicts a woman wearing a pearl earring.

Name: Mona Celica
Desc: It can be called the most beautiful painting of E-02 'Babylonia' so far. (Warning! The description data has been maliciously modified)
